		tears.  "He  told me there was no way I could understand.  Because it was
		about love."</p>

		<p>Suddenly, I understood.  As a psychiatrist, I know that Roz has always had a
		fear of emotional intimacy.  She's afraid of commitment.  But we never
		spoke of it.  We laugh about her preoccupation with sex, but it covers
		something more deeply buried.  And Niles had used his insight into her
		against her  horribly.  Whatever happened the oath?  "First do no harm."</p>

		<p>I wrapped my other arm around her and held her tightly to me as she cried.
