		thought I'd say this to you, Roz Doyle, but I was terribly wrong, and I'm
		very  sorry."</p>

		<p>I smiled at him and gave him a small hug, at which he just stepped back and
		gaped at me.  I laughed.  "Okay, okay, no more of this mushy stuff.  You're
		forgiven.  Go talk to your brother."</p>

		<p>He nodded and was just turning to leave when he thought of something.  "Roz,
		how is Daphne?"</p>

